Subject: [PATCH] doca telemetry: gate plugin on metrics API + add nixl_common_dep

The DOCA telemetry exporter plugin in NIXL has two build problems on
hosts with an older DOCA SDK:

1. ``doca_exporter.cpp`` includes ``common/configuration.h`` which pulls
   in ``<toml++/toml.hpp>``. The tomlplusplus include path is exposed
   through ``nixl_common_dep`` (declared in
   ``src/utils/common/meson.build``) the same way the sibling
   ``prometheus`` exporter wires it up, but the DOCA plugin's
   ``meson.build`` only links ``nixl_infra``. Without ``nixl_common_dep``
   the build fails with::

       fatal error: toml++/toml.hpp: No such file or directory

2. The plugin source uses the metrics-style API
   (``doca_telemetry_exporter_metrics_create_context``,
   ``doca_telemetry_exporter_metrics_add_constant_label``,
   ``doca_telemetry_exporter_metrics_add_label_names``,
   ``doca_telemetry_exporter_metrics_add_counter``,
   ``doca_telemetry_exporter_metrics_add_gauge`` et al., plus the
   ``doca_telemetry_exporter_label_set_id_t`` type) which was
   introduced in newer DOCA releases. Older DOCA SDKs ship
   ``doca_telemetry_exporter.h`` without those symbols, in which case
   the plugin cannot compile.

The current ``meson.build`` only checks that ``doca_telemetry_exporter.h``
exists; we extend the probe to also require the metrics API, and skip
the plugin with an actionable warning if the API is missing. We also add
``nixl_common_dep`` to the plugin's dependency list so the toml++ include
is propagated when the plugin *is* built.

---
diff --git a/src/plugins/telemetry/doca/meson.build b/src/plugins/telemetry/doca/meson.build
index 5bb9422..d8e51f9 100644
--- a/src/plugins/telemetry/doca/meson.build
+++ b/src/plugins/telemetry/doca/meson.build
@@ -14,22 +14,35 @@
 # limitations under the License.
 
 doca_found = false
+doca_has_metrics_api = false
 doca_base_path = '/opt/mellanox/doca'
 doca_inc_path = doca_base_path / 'include'
 doca_arch = host_machine.cpu_family() + '-linux-gnu'
 doca_lib_path = doca_base_path / 'lib' / doca_arch
 
 if cpp.has_header('doca_telemetry_exporter.h', args: '-I' + doca_inc_path)
-    doca_dep = declare_dependency(
-        include_directories: include_directories(doca_inc_path, is_system: true),
-        link_args: [
-            '-L' + doca_lib_path,
-            '-ldoca_telemetry_exporter',
-            '-ldoca_common',
-            '-Wl,-rpath,' + doca_lib_path
-        ]
+    # The plugin source uses the metrics-style API
+    # (doca_telemetry_exporter_metrics_create_context et al.) introduced in
+    # newer DOCA releases. Older DOCA SDKs ship doca_telemetry_exporter.h
+    # without those symbols, in which case the plugin cannot build. Probe
+    # for the label-set type to decide whether to enable it.
+    doca_has_metrics_api = cpp.has_type(
+        'doca_telemetry_exporter_label_set_id_t',
+        prefix: '#include <doca_telemetry_exporter.h>',
+        args: '-I' + doca_inc_path,
     )
-    doca_found = true
+    if doca_has_metrics_api
+        doca_dep = declare_dependency(
+            include_directories: include_directories(doca_inc_path, is_system: true),
+            link_args: [
+                '-L' + doca_lib_path,
+                '-ldoca_telemetry_exporter',
+                '-ldoca_common',
+                '-Wl,-rpath,' + doca_lib_path
+            ]
+        )
+        doca_found = true
+    endif
 endif
 
 if doca_found
@@ -38,12 +51,16 @@ if doca_found
         'doca_plugin.cpp',
         'doca_exporter.cpp',
         include_directories: [nixl_inc_dirs, utils_inc_dirs],
-        dependencies: [nixl_infra, absl_log_dep, doca_dep],
+        dependencies: [nixl_infra, nixl_common_dep, absl_log_dep, doca_dep],
         install: true,
         install_dir: plugin_install_dir,
         name_prefix: '',
     )
     message('Building DOCA telemetry exporter plugin')
+elif doca_has_metrics_api == false and cpp.has_header('doca_telemetry_exporter.h', args: '-I' + doca_inc_path)
+    warning('DOCA Telemetry Exporter headers found but lack the metrics API ' +
+            '(doca_telemetry_exporter_label_set_id_t). DOCA telemetry exporter ' +
+            'will not be built. Upgrade DOCA to a release that exposes the metrics API.')
 else
     warning('DOCA Telemetry Exporter headers not found. DOCA telemetry exporter will not be built.')
 endif
